-- Gas City Ltd. Files for Chapter 11 Bankruptcy With Debt Up to $500 Million
-- B y   E d v a r d   P e t t e r s s o n
-- 2010-10-27T01:14:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-27/gas-city-ltd-files-for-chapter-11-bankruptcy-with-debt-up-to-500-million.html
Gas City Ltd., an independent chain
of fueling stations with locations in Illinois, Indiana, Florida
and Arizona, filed for Chapter 11 bankruptcy court protection.  The company listed assets of $50 million to $100 million
and liabilities of $100 million to $500 million in a filing
today with the U.S. Bankruptcy Court in Chicago.  The family owned and operated company was started in 1966
by its president,  William McEnery , with a location at 55th and
Pulaski streets in Chicago. The company, based in Frankfurt,
Illinois, had more than 50 locations as of January 2009.  The case is In re Gas City, 10-47879, U.S. Bankruptcy
Court, Northern District of Illinois (Chicago.)  To contact the reporter on this story:
Edvard Pettersson in Los Angeles at 
 epettersson@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David E. Rovella at 
 drovella@bloomberg.net . 